Q. At the time that you pulled out your pocket book who was in your company - A. The four prisoners at the bar;
Martin Kilby
, Sharpe and Jone; not Pearce; I took out a one pound note to pay for some liquor that we had; they had all partook of the liquor. I put the pocket book upon the table.

Q. Did she seem in distress - A. Very much so; I said to them, that the strange man had not been gone out above five minutes, they had better go after him. The prisoner, another man, and Mrs. Wilcox, went out; the other man is here;
Caroline Wilcox
and the third person returned in about five or ten minutes. I did not see Dailey return to my knowledge.
